# Important Definitions

## Switch Statement

A decision-making statement that executes one block of code based on the value of an expression.

---

## Case

Represents one possible value inside a switch statement.

---

## Break

Terminates the switch statement after the matching case executes.

---

## Default

Executes when no case matches.

---

## Fall-through

The execution of subsequent cases because the `break` statement is omitted.

---

## Enhanced Switch

A modern switch syntax introduced in Java 14 that uses the `->` operator and prevents fall-through.

